findings.lower_chest: Mild, bibasilar atelectasis. There is no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion.

abdominal_findings.liver: The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout. There is no evidence of focal lesions. There is mild intrahepatic and extrahepatic biliary dilatation.
abdominal_findings.pancreas: The pancreas has normal attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions or pancreatic ductal dilatation.
abdominal_findings.spleen: The spleen shows normal size and attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions.
abdominal_findings.adrenals: The right and left adrenal glands are normal in size and shape.
abdominal_findings.kidneys: The kidneys are of normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram. An 8 mm hypodensity in the lower pole of the right kidney is likely a simple renal cyst.
abdominal_findings.gastrointestinal: There is a small hiatal hernia. Mild thickening of the left lateroconal fascia and mild fat stranding in the region of sigmoid diverticulosis.
abdominal_findings.pelvis: The urinary bladder and distal ureters are unremarkable.
abdominal_findings.reproductive_organs: The uterus is unremarkable. There is a small amount of air within the vagina.
abdominal_findings.lymph_nodes: Multiple, prominent mesenteric lymph nodes do not meet CT size criteria for pathologic enlargement.
abdominal_findings.vascular: There is no abdominal aortic aneurysm. Extensive atherosclerotic disease is noted.
abdominal_findings.bones: There is no evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
abdominal_findings.soft_tissues: There is mild subcutaneous edema in the pelvic wall.
